    "body": "**Describe the bug**\r\n\r\nTools such as [`pip-licenses`](https://github.com/raimon49/pip-licenses) use the LICENSE file included in uploaded Python packages to generate license reports. The latest release of `Cython` does not have a LICENSE file included in some wheels, which makes it more challenging to comply with the license.\r\n\r\nCould a new release of `Cython` be released using the latest `wheel` library that pulls in the LICENSE file? Generally, ensuring that `wheel` is updated to the latest before building the wheel is enough to pull in the LICENSE file as recent versions of `wheel` will automatically look in the root project directory for files named LICENSE*, or COPYING*, etc.\r\n\r\nYou can see the LICENSE missing from the `dist-info` folder of the unzipped wheel:\r\n\r\n```\r\n% ls -l\r\ntotal 8\r\ndrwxr-xr-x@ 20 u  g   640B Oct  1 07:36 Cython/\r\ndrwxr-xr-x@  9 u  g   288B Oct  1 07:36 Cython-0.29.21.dist-info/\r\n-rw-rw-r--@  1 u  g   520B Jun 22  2015 cython.py\r\ndrwxr-xr-x@  5 u  g   160B Oct  1 07:36 pyximport/\r\n% ls -l Cython-0.29.21.dist-info \r\ntotal 104\r\n-rw-rw-r--@ 1 u  g   1.1K Jul  8 21:45 DESCRIPTION.rst\r\n-rw-rw-r--@ 1 u  g   2.6K Jul  8 21:45 METADATA\r\n-rw-rw-r--@ 1 u  g    26K Jul  8 21:45 RECORD\r\n-rw-rw-r--@ 1 u  g   110B Jul  8 21:45 WHEEL\r\n-rw-rw-r--@ 1 u  g   140B Jul  8 21:45 entry_points.txt\r\n-rw-rw-r--@ 1 u  g   1.8K Jul  8 21:45 metadata.json\r\n-rw-rw-r--@ 1 u  g    24B Jul  8 21:45 top_level.txt\r\n```\r\n\r\n**To Reproduce on Ubuntu 18.04**\r\n\r\n\r\n```bash\r\n$ sudo apt install python3-venv\r\n$ python3 -m venv venv\r\n$ source venv/bin/activate\r\n(venv) $ pip install -U pip setuptools wheel\r\n(venv) $ pip install pip-licenses Cython\r\n(venv) $ $ pip freeze --all\r\nCython==0.29.21\r\npip==20.2.3\r\npip-licenses==2.3.0\r\npkg-resources==0.0.0\r\nPTable==0.9.2\r\nsetuptools==50.3.0\r\nwheel==0.35.1\r\n(venv) $ pip-licenses --from=mixed --format=plain-vertical --no-license-path --with-license-file\r\nCython\r\n0.29.21\r\nApache Software License\r\nUNKNOWN\r\n\r\n...\r\n```\r\n\r\n**Expected behavior**\r\n\r\nIt is expected the LICENSE file is included in every wheel and source distribution for Cython. The `UNKNOWN` in the `pip-licenses` command would then be replaced with the contents of `LICENSE.txt`.\r\n\r\nNote: I was able to verify the LICENSE file is included in the Mac wheel, so there just may be a CI setting that needs to get the Linux wheels up to the latest wheel before building.\r\n\r\n**Environment (please complete the following information):**\r\n - OS: Ubuntu 18.04\r\n - Python version: 3.6.9\r\n - Cython version: 0.29.21\r\n",
