            "body": "> Also note how your pip-license command actually prints the right license name, just not its (easy-to-find-elsewhere) content.\r\n\r\nYes, `pip-licenses` finds the license name identified from the trove classifiers. These are properly specified in `setup.py`:\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/cython/cython/blob/af757997c7d13c00b579fd00393350d9367dd12a/setup.py#L271\r\n\r\n> Given that, statistically, no-one on earth reads licenses, allow me to express a scent of doubt in this regard. :)\r\n\r\nI completely agree. It's more for those who want to be sure they are actually abiding by the license when they bundle `Cython` with something they distribute, since even permissive licenses like Apache, require that you retain the license itself when you redistribute.",
